==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Casement
<hw>Case"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Shortened fr. <ets>encasement</ets>. See <er>Incase 1st Case</er>, and cf. <er>Incasement</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A window sash opening on hinges affixed to the upright side of the frame into which it is fitted. <mark>(Poetically)</mark> A window.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>casement</qex> of the great chamber window.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Casemented</ent>⟦br⟧
